	    <h2>FAQ</h2>
	    <h3>What is OpticNav?</h3>
	    <p>OpticNav is an application which displays a user defined map on an augmented reality
        device.</p>
	    
	    <h3>What hardware does the application work on?</h3>
	    <p>The application will work with an Android smart phone or an augmented reality glasses.</p>
        <p>For the best experience, it is highly recommended to use an augmented reality glasses.</p>
	    
	    <h3>Is the application and registration free to use?</h3>
	    <p>Yes, everything is free to use.</p>
	    
	    <h3>How does registering a device work?</h3>
        <p>To register a device you need the application first. The application will give you a</p>
        <p>passcode to place in the text field, this passcode is unique to your device to allow the</p>
        <p>server to register your device to your account.</p>
	    
	    <h3>How do I install the application on my Android device?</h3>
	    <p>Follow the procedure in the <t:link href="/download">Get Application</t:link> page</p>
	    
	    <h3>How do I use this application?</h3>
	    <p>First create an account, and install the application on your device, the application</p>
        <p>can be downloaded from the Download page. Start the application and write down the</p>
        <p>given pass code. Login to your account and go into the Device Manager. In the text box,</p>
        <p>enter the code you retrieved from the application. Once your Android device is registered,</p>
        <p>create a map in the Map Manager page. Use the Instance Manager page to start an instance,</p>
        <p>on your device you can find your instance and start using the application.</p>
	    
	    <h3>Why can't I add more than one device to my account?</h3>
	    <p>For the simple reason that there can't be one person in two different places, at a time.</p>
	    
	    <h3>Can I change my device?</h3>
	    <p>To change devices, you can remove the device at the Device Manager and add a new device.</p>
	    
	    <h3>Where may I read more about the application?</h3>
	    <p>At our <a href="http://ido.atomicpotato.net/opticnav3000/index.php/Table_of_Contents">wiki page</a></p>
	    
